50 km / h: From November 1 in Kiev on 7 highways will limit the speed

01 Nov 2019, 05:00

In Kyiv, starting from November 1, the maximum permissible traffic speed will be 50 km / h on seven roads.
The speed limit is imposed on seven metropolitan roads, where during the warm period allowed to travel up to 80 km / h:

ave. Shukhevych (from the North Bridge to O. Balzak St.);
st. Naberezhnye-Rybalskaya (from Havana Bridge to Electricians Street)
The Dnieper Highway;
Embankment of the highway (from Postal Square to the Dnieper Highway);
Capital Highway (to Zabolotnogo Akademika St.);
st. Saperno-Slobidskaya (from M. Grinchenko St. to the South Bridge);
ave. M. Bazhan (from the Southern Bridge Crossing to Kharkiv Square).

